A anonymous inner class which have no name.
It is used if we have to override method of a Class or Interface
It is of two types
    1. Class ( abstract or concrete )
    2. Interface


// Class 
interface Person(){
    void eat();
}

OR

abstract Person(){
    void eat();
}

public Test{
public static void main(String[] argv){
    Person man = new Person(){
        void eat(){
            System.out.println("eating fast");
        }
    };

    Person woman = new Person(){
        void eat(){
            System.out.println("eating slow");
        }
    };

    man.eat();          // output : eating fast
    woman.eat();        // output : eating slow
}
}
